.TH LOCKSCREEN 1 "2026-05-16" "lockscreen 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lockscreen \- apply a visual effect to the desktop and lock the screen with i3lock
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lockscreen
[\fB\-s\fR \fISIGMA\fR]
[\fB\-r\fR \fIRADIUS\fR]
[\fB\-e\fR \fIEFFECT\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-lock\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lockscreen
captures all connected displays, applies a blur or pixelate effect to the
screenshot, composites multi-monitor setups into a single image, and passes
the result to
.BR i3lock (1).
The temporary image is removed after i3lock exits.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-sigma " " \fISIGMA\fR
Standard deviation for Gaussian blur, or block size (integer) for the
pixelate effect.
A sigma of 1 with pixelate produces no visible change (one-pixel blocks).
Default: \fB1.5\fR.
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-radius " " \fIRADIUS\fR
Spread radius for the asymmetric Gaussian blur.
Has no effect when using the
.B gaussian
or
.B pixelate
effects.
Default: \fB0.1\fR.
.TP
.BR \-e ", " \-\-effect " " \fIEFFECT\fR
Visual effect to apply before locking.
.RS
.TP
.B gaussian
Symmetric Gaussian blur.
.I sigma
controls blur strength.
.TP
.B gaussian\-asymmetric
Asymmetric Gaussian blur with a stretched appearance.
Both
.I sigma
and
.I radius
are used.
.TP
.B pixelate
Pixelate the screenshot.
.I sigma
is cast to an integer and used as the block size in pixels.
.RE
Default: \fBgaussian\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-lock
Capture and apply the effect but do not invoke i3lock.
Prints the path of the saved composite image to stdout instead.
Useful for previewing effect output or scripting.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Exits 0 on success.
Panics (non-zero exit) if screen capture fails, the image cannot be saved to
.IR /tmp ,
or i3lock cannot be executed.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /tmp/lockscreen.png
Temporary composite image.
Deleted automatically after i3lock exits unless
.B \-\-no\-lock
is specified.
.SH EXAMPLES
Lock with default symmetric Gaussian blur:
.PP
.RS
.EX
lockscreen
.EE
.RE
.PP
Lock with a stronger asymmetric blur:
.PP
.RS
.EX
lockscreen \-s 1.5 \-r 2.0 \-e gaussian\-asymmetric
.EE
.RE
.PP
Lock with a coarse pixelate effect (20\-pixel blocks):
.PP
.RS
.EX
lockscreen \-s 20 \-e pixelate
.EE
.RE
.PP
Preview the effect without locking:
.PP
.RS
.EX
lockscreen \-\-no\-lock \-e gaussian\-asymmetric
.EE
.RE
.PP
Typical i3 config binding (mod key = Mod1):
.PP
.RS
.EX
bindsym $mod+Ctrl+Shift+l exec lockscreen \-s 1.5 \-r 2.0 \-e gaussian\-asymmetric
.EE
.RE
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.BR i3lock (1)
must be installed and available on
.BR PATH .
Requires an X11 session managed by
.BR i3 (1)
or
.B i3\-gaps.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR i3lock (1),
.BR i3 (1)
